    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNow that wasm was added for tree-sitter, I think it will be beneficial to have it exposed to lua. Wiring all the nvim API to wasm is not needed, just the fundamental  [WebAssembly](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/WebAssembly/JavaScript_interface) API. \n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe intention is to allow many plugins that now ship c/rust code to use it so plugin devs don't need to build for a gazillion platforms /  users don't need to have compilers installed. \n",
